    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of real estate, is a trust account that holds funds until certain conditions are met, like the sale of a property. It's a safety net to ensure that all parties involved in the transaction fulfill their obligations. You're right, it's a new concept for you, but think of it like a secure, locked chest where your realtor's agent holds the keys to the funds, keeping them safe until the deal is finalized. This way, you can be sure that the funds are protected and won't be used for anything other than the agreed-upon purchase price. \n\nIn Toronto, escrow is a common practice, especially for first-time homebuyers like yourself. It's a bit like a \"giant, magical, underground vault\" where the funds are kept until the closing date, and then, voilà! The funds are released, and the transaction is complete. Your realtor will guide you through the process, making sure everything goes smoothly.",
